    "Hyper-accuracy distortion is the tendency of models to generate responses that may be technically accurate but contextually inappropriate or implausible [6].",
    "The hyper-accuracy distortion is an especially vivid example of a failure of algorithmic fidelity.",
    "The model is supposed to know it is extremely unlikely that a five-year-old child would know the answer to a specific scientific question about galaxy formation or number theory.",
    "So if conditioned to play the part of a child it should not know the answer.",
    "When it goes ahead and answers anyway, that's a failure of algorithmic fidelity."
